	   <tr><td colspan=2>I will agree that when used at the wrong time for the wrong mob that different AoE's really suck. I use different AoE's when soloing and when grouping. My personal favorite are rain type AoE's for grouping when there is more than one tank and they have aggro on multiple mobs. The rain ones are just awesome in this situation because as long as the mob does not move from his spot the aoe will hit multiple times. Point Blank AoE's are best used for farming and AoE bombing groups because they hit an unlimited number of mobs and have realativly high dmg output. Column AoE's are great for solo kiting due to the dmg to mana ratio. Also, has anyone else noticed that the reason why some Al'Kabors aoe's have lower dmg and higher mana cost is that they have extra effects on them like knockback or stun. Personally I haven't used that many of Al'Kabors because I am rarely in a situation where I would use it over another type of AoE.<br>&nbsp;<br>Reality is the fantasy world in which we live - J. Tracy<br>Vymdraven-Dark Elf Wizard<br>Bertox</td></tr>
